      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required to be formally assessed at MRL 2 for Class II device with medium model influence.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is not required at MRL 2 for this device class and model influence level. Simulation setup was reviewed by a senior engineer and standard operating procedures were followed, providing informal control without formal assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required to be formally assessed at MRL 2; model form selection documented.",
      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) was selected based on literature precedent for CFD hemolysis prediction in rotary blood pumps. Formal model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2 but the selection rationale is documented."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
